                     <desc>Circular diagram with Aksum in the center, surrounded by two concentric circles. The first one mentions 8 geographical directions : mǝʿǝrāb, bāḥr, samen, ʾazeb, mǝśrāq, <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC4298Libo">libo</placeName>, dabub, masʾ. The second one mentions 12 provinces of Tǝgrāy : <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3764Hamase">Ḥamāsen</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2019Bur">Bur</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7461Samea">Ṣamǝʾa</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1236Agama">ʾAgāma</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1400AmbaSa">ʾAmbā Śǝnayt</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3307Garalt">Garʿāltā</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2947Endart">ʾƎndartā</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5467Sahart">Saḥart</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1008Abarga">ʾAbargalle</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5882Tamben">Tamben</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5749Sire">Sire</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5575Saraye">Sarāwe</placeName>. </desc>
                  </decoNote>
